The President of the United States issued a statement on the 25th anniversary of Ukrainian independence, expressing pride in joining the Ukrainian people in commemorating this historic event. He acknowledged the challenges Ukraine has faced on its path to independence, including the human chain formed in 1990 and the fallen heroes of the Maidan. The United States, including Ukrainian-Americans, have supported Ukraine in its journey towards independence. The statement reaffirmed the commitment of the United States to stand with Ukraine in protecting its sovereignty and territorial integrity, embracing a strong and united Europe, and promoting democracy, anti-corruption efforts, and human rights. The President offered his best wishes to the people of Ukraine, emphasizing the enduring spirit and freedom of the country.